Take Turn Each turn you can choose which resource to build up. To take a turn, click on a resource and then click the Take Turn button. The top row of numbers represents the total quantity of each resource stored at your farm. The next row represents the current net change in that resource each turn. After you click on a resource, the bottom row will update so you know exactly what will happen on the turn.

Absolute Value of Sine Reduce theta so that \gcd(a,b)=1 where \theta = \frac{a\pi}{b}. What is the denominator? What is \sin(\frac{\pi}{b})? If b=1,2,3,4, or 6 and a is integer with gcd(a,b)=1 then \sin(\frac{a\pi}{b})=\pm \sin(\frac{\pi}{b}). Positive or Negative? For cosine, is \frac{a\pi}{b} on left or right? For sine, is \frac{a\pi}{b} on top or bottom? Add or subtract \frac{2b\pi}{b} until -b\lt a\lt b.
